      "side": 1,
      "message": "Could you explain the exact use case for this approach?​‌\n\nAlso, the IP set via `SIOCSIFADDR` ioctl is only applied in the kernel at runtime and is not persisted anywhere. It will be lost after a reboot, right?",
      "revId": "c78a2516c1de252b8c79e86d81e3f748b9c3be85",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
